

Frontend: React.js, Axios (for end points)
Backend: Node.js, Express.js, MongoDB
Authentication: JWT (JSON Web Tokens)




user signs in via JWT, which returns a token for authorization.
Token is included in the request headers 

Task CRUD Operations:

The frontend sends HTTP requests (using Axios) to the backend API to manage tasks (create, update, delete).
The backend performs the necessary database operations (using Mongoose) and responds with the appropriate data or status.

Task updates are reflected immediately in the UI.